OL,6,FIn its report on 100 phrases which
OL,7,Fshow how the English language is
OL,8,Fchanging, they said that whilst
OL,9,Fclassic idioms such as "kill two birds
OL,10,Fwith one stone" remain widely used,
OL,11,Fnewer phrases are gaining momentum.
OL,13,F"No cap", meaning no lie or I'm
OL,14,Fserious, was the most popular of the
OL,15,F100 phrases for Gen Z.
