OL,3,C'No cap': the slang terms 'kicking the
OL,4,Cbucket'
OL,6,FFirst used in 2011, the slang term
OL,7,Fcomes from African American English
OL,8,Fwhere "cap" means exaggeration or
OL,9,Ffalsehood and is used across the
OL,10,Fgenerations, the study found, but most
OL,11,Fprominently by Gen Z.
OL,13,FOther phrases are being replaced by
OL,14,Fmodern alternatives as younger
OL,15,Fgenerations embrace the shift.
