OL,6,F"Spill the beans" was first recorded
OL,7,Fin 1919, the report said, but saw a
OL,8,Fsurge in the 1990s. The British
OL,9,FCouncil says the rise in social media
OL,10,Fis partly to blame for the rising
OL,11,Fpopularity of similar phrase, "spill
OL,12,Fthe tea" - an idiom popular with gen Z.
OL,14,FSome phrases like "step up to the
OL,15,Fplate" and "below the belt" are
OL,16,Ffrequently used among older
OL,17,Fgenerations but could be falling out
OL,18,Fof fashion as they're rarely seen in
OL,19,Finternet comment sections which skew
OL,20,Fto a younger audience.
