OL,6,FThe British Council said the phrase
OL,7,F"bucket list", meaning a list of
OL,8,Fthings to do before you die, was
OL,9,F"practically unheard of" until 2007,
OL,10,Fwhen comedy-adventure film The Bucket
OL,11,FList was released.
OL,13,FIt is thought to have come from
OL,14,Fanother idiom: "to kick the bucket".
